html
    head
        title= apptitle
        link(
            rel = 'stylesheet'
            href = 'https://cdnjs.cloudflare.com/ajax/libs/twitter-bootstrap/3.3.7/css/bootstrap.min.css'
        )
        
        
    body
        div(class='container')
            div(class='jumbotron')
                h1= pagetitle                
                
            blockquote
                h2 User stories
                br
                p 1) I can pass a URL as a parameter and I will receive a shortened URL in the JSON response'
                p 2) If I pass an invalid URL that does not follow the valid http://www.example.com format, the JSON response will contain an error instead
                p 3) When I visit that shortened URL, it will redirect me to my original link
                
            h2 Example
            br
            p base URL :
            code https://url-shortener-service-56.herokuapp.com/ 
            br
            br
            p adding the following URL to shorten to base URL (the app only takes .net, .com. org extensions) :
            code https://www.google.com
            br
            br
            p will output :
            code { "original_url":"https://www.google.com", "short_url":"https://url-shortener-service-56.herokuapp.com/8170" }
            br
            br
            p Now, the following URL :
            code https://url-shortener-service-56.herokuapp.com/8170
            br
            br
            p will redirect to :
            code https://www.google.com
            